<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>Priority Postseason Ticket Requests Open Now</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/17/baseball-priority-postseason-ticket-requests-open-now</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/17/baseball-priority-postseason-ticket-requests-open-now</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Kendrick Family Ballpark Fans" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/17/RMB_2975.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – As the West Virginia University baseball team continues to stay in the hunt for the 17th NCAA Tournament bid in program history, the Mountaineer Ticket Office has made online NCAA postseason tickets requests available should the Mountaineers be selected to host an NCAA Regional, May 29-June 1 and/or Super Regional, June 5-8 at Kendrick Family Ballpark.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/RMB_2975.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/RMB_2975.jpg"><media:title>Kendrick Family Ballpark Fans</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/RMB_2975.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 12:07:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59110</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU Golf Set to Begin Play at Marana Regional</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/17/wvu-golf-headed-to-marana-regional</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/17/wvu-golf-headed-to-marana-regional</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The WVU golf team is ready to begin competition at the NCAA Regional" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/17/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_NCAAReg.jpg" /><br /><br />MARANA, Ariz. – The West Virginia University golf team will make its return to NCAA Regionals as the Mountaineers will head to the Marana Regional at The Gallery Golf Club in Marana, Arizona, from May 18-20.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_NCAAReg.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_NCAAReg.jpg"><media:title>The WVU golf team is ready to begin competition at the NCAA Regional</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_NCAAReg.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 09:55:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>5</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59109</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Earn Four All-Big 12 Honors at Outdoor Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/17/track-field-mountaineers-earn-four-all-big-12-honors-at-outdoor-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/17/track-field-mountaineers-earn-four-all-big-12-honors-at-outdoor-championships</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Joy Naukot competing in the 10,000m meters at the Big 12 Outdoor Championships" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/17/IMG_3350.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University track and field team earned four All-Big 12 honors at the 2026 Big 12 Conference Outdoor Championships in Tucson, Arizona.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/IMG_3350.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/IMG_3350.jpeg"><media:title>Joy Naukot competing in the 10,000m meters at the Big 12 Outdoor Championships</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/IMG_3350.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 00:14:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59108</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Rally to Defeat TCU in Regular Season Finale</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/16/baseball-mountaineers-rally-to-defeat-tcu-in-regular-season-finale</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/16/baseball-mountaineers-rally-to-defeat-tcu-in-regular-season-finale</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Brodie Kresser celebrates after hitting a double against TCU" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/16/G3_KU-146.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 9 West Virginia University baseball team defeated TCU, 6-4, Saturday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark to conclude the regular season. The Mountaineers improve to 37-13 and 21-9 in the Big 12 while the Horned Frogs fall to 33-20 and 17-13 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/G3_KU-146.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/G3_KU-146.jpg"><media:title>Brodie Kresser celebrates after hitting a double against TCU</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/G3_KU-146.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2026 16:54:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59107</s:story_id></item><item><title>Rowing Returns to Sarasota for Big 12 Championship</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/16/rowing-returns-to-sarasota-for-big-12-championship</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/16/rowing-returns-to-sarasota-for-big-12-championship</guid><category>Rowing</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="A graphic preview the 2026 Big 12 Rowing Championship" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/16/ROW26_RaceDay_Big12_1920X1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University rowing team will compete at the 2026 Big 12 Championship on Sunday, May 17, at Nathan Benderson Park in Sarasota, Florida.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/ROW26_RaceDay_Big12_1920X1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/ROW26_RaceDay_Big12_1920X1080.jpg"><media:title>A graphic preview the 2026 Big 12 Rowing Championship</media:title></media:content><enclosur